Thanks for following up, Parent_D—happy to share more.

1) Typical daily schedule (example day)
- Arrival & settling-in: ~8:00–9:00 (greeting, free play, check-ins)
- Morning circle: ~9:00–9:20 (songs, stories, calendar/weather)

- Reliable communication (especially around health, sleep, transitions)
- Participation in periodic check-ins/parent conferences
Optional opportunities include helping with a special event, sharing a cultural tradition/story, or joining an occasional classroom activity—only if your schedule allows.

3) When places are limited, what we prioritize
We mainly look at practical fit and stability for the child and classroom:
- Schedule fit (days/hours) and start date
- Consistent attendance and ability to follow health/safety policies
- Readiness for our routines (with a supportive transition plan)
- Strong family–school partnership (responsiveness and alignment on expectations)

If you’re open to sharing, it would help to know: (a) your ideal drop-off/pick-up window and days needed, (b) your child’s age and nap routine, and (c) any key needs (e.g., separation anxiety support, allergies, language environment).
